==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Turnix
<hw>Tur"nix</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. L.
<ets>coturnix</ets> a quail.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any one of
numerous species of birds belonging to <gen>Turnix</gen> or
<gen>Hemipodius</gen> and allied genera of the family
<fam>Turnicidae</fam>. These birds resemble quails and partridges in
general appearance and in some of their habits, but differ in important
anatomical characteristics. The hind toe is usually lacking. They are
found in Asia, Africa, Southern Europe, the East Indian Islands, and
esp. in Australia and adjacent islands, where they are called
<altname>quails</altname> (see <er>Quail</er>, <pos>n.</pos>, 3.). See
<er>Turnicimorphae</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Turnkey</ent>⟦br⟧
